This paper focuses on software development processes and techniques to improve code quality and reduce side effects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the use of structured and templated code, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The study evaluates the performance of the proposed method on large enterprise-level applications, which falls under the category of software development (cs.SD). The paper also discusses the use of metrics to evaluate the performance of the proposed method, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY).
